&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12924373" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 24 Oct 2010 19:56:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The only way I figure peek() could fail is if the LinkedList was being used in a non-thread safe manner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12924374" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 24 Oct 2010 19:58:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep - a quick look shows that &quot;runners&quot; is normally synchronized on itself, but it&apos;s not in&lt;br/&gt;
blockUntilFinished&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12924379" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 24 Oct 2010 20:13:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that synchronizes on runners only enough to call peek()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013107" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 15:45:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 3.1.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
